6666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvelondrasedai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VelondraSedai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/8/02 10:28:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=861.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> It is very enjoyable to see that EQ has some philosophers</span><hr size=1> This has been kicking around the board for sometime and i feel the urge to have my own say about it.  I have to agree with the last few posts. Though it makes me insanely jealous to think of someone making 80k off an item, it was his item to do as he pleased with.<br>
<br>
 Though he may have said he wanted it for a cloak, then tryed to sell it, then said he woudl use it for a cloak... Would it have really made any difference to you guys attending the raid if he had just not mentioned what he wanted it for at all? Since you all attended, and he told you all many times that he got the first scale, it is his. Though I cannot speak for others, were I live we hold a democratic government wherein one's property is owned solely by themself. Once that scale dropped it became his property as was pre-agreed by all in attendance. A person (in America) has the right to do what they choose with their property. So if he said that he would make a cloak, then decided to sell it he did not steal anything. The worst that can be said is that he lied, but in fact he probably just had the scale in his bag and begain to think if he really wanted the cloak or 80k, the pp to most likely upgrade all of his equiptment and choose the 80k. Which ever happened, it is his scale and did not ever belong to the raid party. It is thusly no bussiness of the raid party or anyone else to decide what happens with it. <br>
<br>
 However, none of this is to say that I agree with reserving an item that is not even a part of your epic on a raid. But would I attend a raid with an item reserved? Probably. Would I reserve an item not for my epic on a raid I lead? No. It is a matter of each person's own idea of ethics and their own philosophies. Having said this i truely hope that everyone will realize that it is done and over with almost a month ago, and that what ever happened has happened. As much as I enjoy reading some of the well layed out arguments here, I hope that this can be simply forgotten soon. <br>
<br>
